          using a corpus approach doesn't necessarily mean compiling  a load of text and using a concordancer;

as you have done already photocopying transcripts and asking students to gap fill, identify words, structures is just as good if not better in a lot of ways :)

raising students ability to notice language is the key, the rest of the corpora approach is more or less the icing :)

if you want to sort according to frequency you can use following command lines (hat tip to developer):
$ src/mwelist.py data.sst > counts.tsv $ sort -t$'\t' -k3,3 -n -r counts.tsv
Or the TSV file can be opened in a spreadsheet application for sorting.
